<h2 id="toc_1.1" class="justcenter">Building your own services on aws</h2>

<h3 id="toc_1.1.1">Basic Setup</h3>
<ul>
<li>
Lanuching base OS

<ol>
<li>
Lanuches a t1.micro instance(amazon linux ami) on aws tokyo region using prepared ssh key.(a reserved t1.micro insntace: 105 Dollars/3years)

<li>
Security Group: ssh(22) only, no icmp(no ping response).

<li>
Attaches a EIP(Global IPV4:  54.249.118.215) to the instance.

<li>
Registers a domain name cgeeker.com from <a href="http://www.onamae.com">onamae</a>.(920 YEN * 3years = 2760 YEN)

<li>
Binds www.rollingbedsheet.com to EIP. (A record, dns01: i will build a DNS Server)

<li>
Allocates 32GB EBS to root and resize it by <code>resize2fs /dev/sda1</code>.

</ol>
</ul>

<ul>
<li>
Customizing the OS

<ol>
<li>
Enables epel repository. <code>/etc/yum.repos.d/epel.repo</code>

<li>
Modifies deamon service only left some services like this: <code>chkconfig --list | grep 3:on</code>
<pre>
atd                     0:off   1:off   2:off   3:on    4:on    5:on    6:off
blk-availability        0:off   1:on    2:on    3:on    4:on    5:on    6:off
cloud-init              0:off   1:off   2:on    3:on    4:on    5:on    6:off
cloud-init-user-scripts 0:off   1:off   2:on    3:on    4:on    5:on    6:off
crond                   0:off   1:off   2:on    3:on    4:on    5:on    6:off
iptables                0:off   1:off   2:on    3:on    4:on    5:on    6:off
irqbalance              0:off   1:off   2:off   3:on    4:on    5:on    6:off
lvm2-monitor            0:off   1:on    2:on    3:on    4:on    5:on    6:off
network                 0:off   1:off   2:on    3:on    4:on    5:on    6:off
ntpd                    0:off   1:off   2:on    3:on    4:on    5:on    6:off
rsyslog                 0:off   1:off   2:on    3:on    4:on    5:on    6:off
sshd                    0:off   1:off   2:on    3:on    4:on    5:on    6:off
sysstat                 0:off   1:on    2:on    3:on    4:on    5:on    6:off
</pre>

<li>
Sets hostname
<pre>
HOSTNAME=www.rollingbedsheet.com #/etc/sysconfig/network
</pre>
<pre>
domain cgeeker.com #/etc/resolv.conf
</pre>

<li>
Disables ipv6
<pre>
install ipv6 /bin/true #/etc/modprobe.d/disable-ipv6.conf, replace the installation of ipv6 with /bin/true
</pre>
<pre>
NETWORKING_IPV6=no
IPV6INIT=no
IPV6_ROUTER=no
IPV6_AUTOCONF=no
IPV6FORWARDING=no
IPV6TO4INIT=no
IPV6_CONTROL_RADVD=no
</pre>

</ol>
</ul>

